<br>
One of the reasons is the riduclous golem wand exploit where you can sell them to a vendor and get them back charged (have to sell a charged one first then the empty ones). I spent lvl's 22 to 36 in cazic thule so I have around 25 golem wands in my bank. Almost every wizard has J-boots that I've fought so I make sure I'm using sow potions with the boots as backup. If I spam one or two wands on a wizard it ensures no buff will be up for long and I've noticed most wizards I've fought lack a permenant see invis item (and no-one is stupid enough to have that familiar up for a duel). So my basic strategy is to strip all buffs I can, then charge up as fast as I can hitting hide every time it refreshes to clear the target box and click on the golem wands as I rush the wizard. This mixed with good resists seems to go over fairly well. Mind you I've gotten my butt handed to me several times by wizards 56+, but I tell myself its due to the level difference to help boost my fragile ego.<br>
<br>
Bottom line is that verant needs to remove the golem wand and pre-nerf pummice exploits. They make several caster battles trivial (coupled with very good resists) so I don't feel bad at all when a wizard uses terrain or lev to gank me.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp<br>
